INSERT INTO `course` (`ID`,`school`,`major`,`number`,`units`,`name`,`description`,`semester`) VALUES (27,'Dornsife','AMST','350',4,'Junior Seminar in American Studies and Ethnicity: Theories and Methods','Advanced study in interdisciplinary theories and methods for analyzing race and ethnicity in the United Stes, including a comparative study of topics such as inequality, gender, and class.',1);
INSERT INTO `course` (`ID`,`school`,`major`,`number`,`units`,`name`,`description`,`semester`) VALUES (28,'Dornsife','AMST','357m',4,'Latino Social Movements','Focuses on the political experience of Latinos in the U.S. Comparative analysis of their political experiences and perspectives, their histories of identity formation, and their political organizations.',1);
INSERT INTO `course` (`ID`,`school`,`major`,`number`,`units`,`name`,`description`,`semester`) VALUES (29,'Dornsife','AMST','392',2,'Undergraduate Research Methods','Examination of processes of scholarly research; quantitative and qualitative research methods; faculty mentorship; experiential learning; research proposal writing; careers in research. Sophomore or junior standing in the major. Departmental approval.',1);
INSERT INTO `course` (`ID`,`school`,`major`,`number`,`units`,`name`,`description`,`semester`) VALUES (30,'Dornsife','AMST','442',4,'American Literature, 1920 to the Present','American poetry, fiction, and drama since World War I with special attention to Eliot, Frost, Hemingway, Fitzgerald, O\'Neill, Stevens, Faulkner, and Nabokov.',1);
INSERT INTO `course` (`ID`,`school`,`major`,`number`,`units`,`name`,`description`,`semester`) VALUES (31,'Dornsife','AMST','444m',4,'Native American Literature','Survey of Native American literature, including oral traditions and print genres, such as short story, poetry, novel, and autobiography, from 1700 to the present. <strong>Recommended preparation:</strong> ENGL 263.',1);
